OL,3,CPolice widows forced to choose between
OL,4,Clove and financial security
OL,6,FRichard Critchley, from the National
OL,7,FAssociation of Retired Police
OL,8,FOfficers, said: It's not a question of
OL,9,Fwhether they cost it or not. It's a
OL,10,Fquestion of human rights. It's the
OL,11,Fhuman right of a person, it's the UN
OL,12,FInternational right of a person to
OL,13,Fmarry and they are denied.
OL,15,F"They are put in a situation of
OL,16,Floneliness, of being on their own and
OL,17,Fsuffering. I can tell you of other
OL,18,Fpeople we've spoken to one
OL,19,Fcontemplated suicide on more than one
OL,20,Foccasion.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/9
